# Definition of Done

## A task is done when:
1. `npm run build` passes
2. The page renders **real data** (not placeholders, not zeros, not empty sections)
3. You have a **screenshot** proving it renders correctly (Playwright: `npx playwright screenshot --browser chromium "http://localhost:PORT/page" /path/to/screenshot.png --viewport-size 1400,900`)
4. For UI changes: mobile screenshot too (390x844)
5. No console errors in the browser

## Visual confirmation is mandatory for any change users can see
- Screenshot BEFORE presenting work as done
- If it doesn't look right, fix it first
- curl returning 200 is NOT visual confirmation

## Never
- Mark done without a screenshot of the rendered page
- Skip verification "to save time"
- Say "it builds" as proof it works